past errors and to abandon everything in our lives that does not meet with Hashem’s favor.\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <*24>}24{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}Bamidbar 28:9±10.\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <*25>}25{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}Bamidbar 29:1±2.\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <*26>}26{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}Bamidbar 29:3±6.\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <*27>}27{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}Bamidbar 23:21. These words were uttered by Bilaam when he was asked to curse the 
