{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <*77>}77{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}This refers to the Book in which the righteous are inscribed for life everlasting.\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <*78>}78{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}We ask Hashem to grant us life for His sake, i.e., so that we can fulfill His commandments.\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <*79>}79{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}We proclaim and accept His Kingship on Rosh Hashana.\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <*80>}80{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}He helps us during the Ten Days of Penitence, by accepting our repentance.\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <*81>}81{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}He delivers us on Yom Kippur by forgiving our sins.\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <*82>}82{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}On Sukkos, as His Divine Cloud of Glory, hovers over us, He shields us from spiritual and 
physical danger (Shaare Shomayim).\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <*83>}83{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}Hashem’s rule of the world is permanent and perpetual (Kuzari).\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <*84>}84{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}Here we emphatically declare our belief in the immortality of the soul (Kuzari).\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <*85>}85{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}Deliverance is not a sudden happening but rather a process of growth or sprouting.\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <*86>}86{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}Even if we are not worthy of life by virtue of our deeds, inscribe us for life because You are 
a merciful Father (Siddur Chasidei Ashkenaz).\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <*87>}87{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}The word {\highlight7 @hh}{\highlight7 <HEB>}\rtlch \'e5\'cc\'e1\'c0\'eb\'c5\'ef{\highlight7 {\ltrch @ee}}{\highlight7 {\ltrch<}{\ltrch ENG}{\ltrch>}}\ltrch , ‘and so,’ marks the beginning of the special prayers of the Shemoneh Esreh 
