{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <*21>}21{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}Hashem gives them every opportunity to repent.\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <*22>}22{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 @hh}{\highlight7 <HEB>}\rtlch \'ec\'c8\'e7\'c7\'f9\'d1{\highlight7 {\ltrch @ee}}{\highlight7 {\ltrch<}{\ltrch ENG}{\ltrch>}}\ltrch  is a word used in reference to prayer. See Yeshaya 26:16, “{\highlight7 @hh}{\highlight7 <HEB>}\rtlch \'f6\'c8\'f7\'e5\'cc\'ef \'ec\'c7\'e7\'c7\'f9\'d1{\highlight7 {\ltrch @ee}}{\highlight7 {\ltrch<}{\ltrch ENG}{\ltrch>}}\ltrch , they poured out a 
