welfare.—S.R. Hirsch\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <*35>}35{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}“Yaakov” refers to all of Yisrael, the true descendants of the patriarch Yaakov.—Radak\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <*36>}36{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}Assaf was one of the ten composers who contributed to the Book of Tehillim; he wrote 
eleven psalms (73±83). The leading Levite musician of his times, he was also endowed with the 
spirit of prophecy.\par
